==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|incrementum|lang=la}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The action of [[increasing]] or becoming greater.
#* Woodward
#*: the seminary that furnisheth matter for the formation and '''increment''' of animal and vegetable bodies
#* Coleridge
#*: A nation, to be great, ought to be compressed in its '''increment''' by nations more civilized than itself.
# {{context|heraldry|lang=en}} The [[wax|waxing]] of the moon.
# The [[amount]] of [[increase]].
# {{context|rhetoric|lang=en}} An [[amplification]] without strict [[climax]], as in the following passage: "Finally, brethren, whatsoever things are true, whatsoever things are honest, whatsoever things are just, whatsoever things are pure, whatsoever things are lovely, whatsoever things are of good report, {{...}} think on these things."

